</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <div class="ti">&#127885; BHGS Licensed #A49573</div>
    <div class="ti">&#128297; OEM Parts &middot; All Brands</div>
    <div class="ti">&#9889; Same Day Service</div>
    <div class="ti">&#128293; Vent Inspection Included</div>
    <div class="ti">&#128737; 90-Day Warranty</div>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>Labor and parts quoted separately &mdash; and a clogged vent is often the whole story</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Most appliance repair companies in Los Angeles use flat-rate BlueBook pricing &mdash; a single bundled number before diagnosis. For dryer repairs, that approach is particularly problematic because the most common dryer problem in LA &mdash; a clogged vent causing slow drying or a blown thermal fuse &mdash; often requires no replacement parts at all. A flat rate bundles in part costs you won&rsquo;t actually need.</p>
      <p>We diagnose first. If the problem is a blocked vent, we clear it and inspect the thermal fuse. If the fuse blew from the heat buildup, we replace it &mdash; but more importantly, we find out why it blew. A thermal fuse blows for a reason. Replacing it without clearing the vent just means it blows again in three months.</p>
      <p>The $89 diagnostic fee covers the full diagnosis. After that you get two numbers: labor and the specific part needed (if any). You see both before approving anything.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="warning-block">
      <div class="warning-label">&#9888; Fire hazard &mdash; clogged dryer vents in LA</div>
      <p>Clogged dryer vents are one of the leading causes of residential fires in the US. In LA, longer vent runs in apartment buildings and older homes compound the risk. If your dryer takes two or three cycles to dry a normal load, the vent is likely the issue &mdash; and it&rsquo;s a safety problem, not just an efficiency one. We inspect vent condition on every dryer service call.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="transparency-block">
      <div class="tr-card them">
        <h3>Flat-Rate BlueBook pricing</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
          <li>Single price before diagnosis</li>
          <li>Labor and parts bundled regardless of what&rsquo;s needed</li>
          <li>Vent clearing included in a padded flat rate</li>
          <li>You pay for parts you may not need</li>
          <li>Root cause may go unfixed</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="tr-card us">
        <h3>Our approach &mdash; labor + parts separate</h3>
        <ul class="tr-list">
          <li>Diagnose first, including vent inspection</li>
          <li>Labor and parts shown as separate line items</li>
          <li>No-part repairs cost less &mdash; you see why</li>
          <li>Root cause found and fixed, not just symptoms</li>
          <li>$89 diagnostic applied to the total</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Labor Rates by Repair Type &mdash; Los Angeles 2026</p>
    <h2>What dryer repair labor costs in Los Angeles</h2>
    <p class="lead">All prices are labor only. Parts quoted separately after diagnosis. $89 diagnostic applied to repair total when you approve the work.</p>
    <div class="price-table-wrap">
      <table class="price-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Repair Type</th><th>Labor Range</th><th>What&rsquo;s Typically Involved</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="highlight-row">
            <td><div class="repair-type">Takes too long to dry <span class="fire-badge">FIRE RISK</span></div><div class="repair-desc">Two or three cycles for a normal load, clothes damp after full cycle</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$150&ndash;$320</div><div class="price-parts-note">Often no parts needed</div></td>
            <td>Dryer vent cleaning and inspection (most common cause in LA). If thermal fuse also blew from heat buildup, added as separate line item.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Not heating / clothes stay wet</div><div class="repair-desc">Drum turns but no heat produced</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$150&ndash;$340</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ heating element or gas components</div></td>
            <td>Heating element (electric), thermal fuse, high-limit thermostat, cycling thermostat, gas valve coils (gas dryers)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Not starting / no power</div><div class="repair-desc">No response, display dead, won&rsquo;t begin cycle</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$150&ndash;$300</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ parts if needed</div></td>
            <td>Door switch, thermal fuse, start switch, control board, power supply board</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Drum not turning</div><div class="repair-desc">Heats but drum stationary, or drum wobbling</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$180&ndash;$360</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ belt or rollers</div></td>
            <td>Drive belt (most common), drum support rollers, idler pulley, motor</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Loud squeaking / grinding</div><div class="repair-desc">Squealing during tumble, grinding or thumping</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$160&ndash;$340</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ parts</div></td>
            <td>Drum support rollers, drum bearing or glides, worn belt, blower wheel obstruction</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Overheating / shutting off mid-cycle</div><div class="repair-desc">Gets too hot, trips thermal cutoff, stops mid-load</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$150&ndash;$300</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ thermal cutoff if blown</div></td>
            <td>Vent blockage (root cause), thermal cutoff fuse replacement, cycling thermostat. We address the blockage first.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
