            <td><div class="price-labor">$160&ndash;$340</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ igniter and/or gas valve coils</div></td>
            <td>Igniter replacement, radiant sensor, gas valve coil set. We confirm gas supply is reaching the valve before diagnosing igniter.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Error code / control board failure</div><div class="repair-desc">Persistent error codes, erratic operation</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$240&ndash;$480</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ board (expensive on some brands)</div></td>
            <td>Main control board or user interface board. Diagnosis confirms board vs. sensor or wiring first.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="luxury-row">
            <td><div class="repair-type">Miele / Bosch <span class="luxury-badge">LUXURY</span></div><div class="repair-desc">All failure types</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$280&ndash;$560+</div><div class="price-parts-note">+ OEM parts (premium pricing)</div></td>
            <td>European-sourced OEM components, proprietary diagnostic protocols, heat pump dryers require specialized handling</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><div class="repair-type">Diagnostic fee</div><div class="repair-desc">Service call + full diagnosis including vent inspection</div></td>
            <td><div class="price-labor">$89</div><div class="price-parts-note">Applied to repair</div></td>
            <td>Applied to labor total when you approve the repair. If no repair &mdash; you pay $89.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="table-note"><strong>All prices are labor only.</strong> Parts quoted separately as a line item after diagnosis. Vent clearing and inspection included when relevant &mdash; not a separate charge. Quote before we start; invoice matches the quote. 90-day warranty on parts and labor.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Cost Factors</p>
    <h2>What affects dryer repair cost in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="factors-grid">
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128293;</div><h3>Vent length and routing</h3><p>LA apartment buildings often have long vent runs &mdash; sometimes 15&ndash;25 feet with multiple bends. Longer runs are harder to clear and more prone to blockage. We inspect the full vent run as part of every dryer service call.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128200;</div><h3>Gas vs. electric</h3><p>Electric dryers fail most often with heating elements and thermal fuses. Gas dryers have igniter and gas valve coil failures in addition. Gas repairs involve confirming safe gas supply before diagnosis &mdash; which is factored into labor.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127991;</div><h3>Brand and part availability</h3><p>Standard brands (Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, GE) have heating elements and belts available same-day. Miele heat pump dryers use European-sourced components at premium pricing &mdash; which is why parts are quoted separately.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128218;</div><h3>Stacked unit access</h3><p>Stacked dryers in WeHo and Silver Lake apartments require removing the unit or accessing from below in tight spaces. This adds labor time and is reflected in the quote before we start work.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#128197;</div><h3>Age of the unit</h3><p>Drum rollers, belts, and bearings on older units (10+ years) may come as kits rather than individual parts. We quote the kit cost separately so you see exactly what&rsquo;s being replaced and why.</p></div>
      <div class="factor-card"><div class="factor-icon">&#127968;</div><h3>Root cause vs. symptom</h3><p>A thermal fuse replacement without clearing the vent that caused it to blow is a repair that fails again in 90 days. We find and fix the cause. The separate labor and parts breakdown shows you exactly what each fix costs.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">Repair vs. Replace</p>
    <h2>When to repair a dryer, when to replace it</h2>
    <p class="lead">We give you an honest assessment after diagnosis. Dryers are one of the most cost-effective appliances to repair &mdash; the math almost always favors repair.</p>
    <div class="rvr-grid">
      <div class="rvr-card repair">
        <h3>Repair makes sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Unit is under 12 years old</li>
          <li>Single component failure &mdash; belt, heating element, thermal fuse</li>
          <li>Total repair (labor + parts) is under 50% of replacement value</li>
          <li>Stacked unit &mdash; replacement plus installation is expensive</li>
          <li>Miele or Bosch heat pump dryer &mdash; these last 15+ years</li>
          <li>The failure is vent-related (often no parts cost)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="rvr-card replace">
        <h3>Replace makes more sense when:</h3>
        <ul class="rvr-list">
          <li>Budget dryer is 12&ndash;15+ years old</li>
          <li>Drum bearing or motor failed on an old unit</li>
          <li>Control board cost exceeds 60% of replacement value</li>
          <li>Multiple components failing simultaneously</li>
          <li>Parts discontinued with no reliable ETA</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

