    <p class="sl">FAQ</p>
    <h2>Questions about dryer repair costs in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does dryer repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor typically runs $150&ndash;$340 for standard brands. Parts are quoted separately after diagnosis. The most common LA dryer problem &mdash; a clogged vent &mdash; often requires no replacement part. The $89 diagnostic fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why does my dryer take so long to dry clothes?</div><div class="faq-a">The most common cause in LA is a clogged dryer vent. Lint restricts airflow, the dryer can&rsquo;t exhaust heat, and a normal load takes two or three cycles. It&rsquo;s also a fire hazard. We clear the vent and inspect the thermal fuse on every slow-dryer call. In many cases no part is needed.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is dryer vent cleaning included in the repair?</div><div class="faq-a">When a vent blockage is causing or contributing to the failure, clearing it is part of the repair &mdash; not a separate charge. We also inspect the full vent run and let you know if the duct routing needs attention. A thermal fuse blows for a reason. We find the cause.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why do you quote labor and parts separately?</div><div class="faq-a">Many LA repair companies use flat-rate BlueBook pricing. A vent-clearing job with no parts needed should not cost the same as a heating element replacement. We quote separately so the price reflects your actual repair &mdash; and many dryer repairs cost less than homeowners expect.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are parts included in the quoted labor price?</div><div class="faq-a">No &mdash; all prices on this page are labor only. After diagnosis we quote the specific part needed as a separate line item. You see both numbers before approving anything. OEM parts used wherever available.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the $89 diagnostic fee?</div><div class="faq-a">We charge $89 to come out and diagnose the problem, including vent inspection. That fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work. If you decide not to repair, you pay $89 and we leave.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What warranty do you provide on dryer repair?</div><div class="faq-a">90 days on parts and labor. Same issue within 90 days &mdash; we come back at no charge. OEM parts wherever available.</div></div>
    </div>
